data.title: A Diner In Every Sense Of The Word!
data.text: From the moment you pull up, you know you are at a diner. Walking in, you aren't disappointed. Everything you expect a diner to be, this is: old waitresses, cheesy decorations on the walls, and food that is just this side of greasy. You will leave satisfied, and won't pay a lot for it.

data.title: If you serve beans and franks for a main meal , it must be good !
data.text:
I had a job to complete 3 doors down from here. I finished the job and I 
Walked over to this hole in the place. On the windows they had pictures of
Different meals that they served. One picture was beans and Franks . It sounds
Like my kinda place. Just missed the lunch rush and this place was still hopping.
I was seated quickly and got a big ole glass of iced tea . Then I ordered beans
And franks ..that hit the spot. I received my food quickly, food was hot and good. Even had fresh cornbread with my meal. (REMINDS ME OF TEXAS).I WILL RETURN
Next time I'm in town. Promise  .

data.title: Greatest Hole in the Wall
data.text: This is one southern / soul food tasty hole in the wall dinner like restaurant.  The food is fresh and really good and the staff is just amazing.  The hospitality is just what a girl from the north need.  I got the Jimmy's Breakfast Combo (Waffle with strawberries, Eggs and Potatoes).  And the coffee was the best I've ever had.  It would be really nice if they took a moment to wipe down the window seals but if one can get past that, then your experience will be wonderful

data.title: Suprised (in a good way)!
data.text:
This place was recommended by a student at the local university, so we decided to give it a try.  The atmosphere on the outside is much to be desired and very much that of a diner, but the smiles that greeted us inside the doors were warm, friendly and welcoming.  
Homemade vegetable barley soup was delish, we also tried the egg salad, BLT and grilled cheese with tomato and pickles sandwiches and they were all  to large for us to finish!  Overall great lunch and hope to eat there again next time we travel that way!

data.title: Better than most diners
data.text: I have eaten at this restaurant many times including brf, lunch and dinner and I have never been disappointed. Jimmy's is a diner with a varied menu of standard American food. The quality is good and the food is  consistent. It is a good place to go to when you do not want to cook. They also have take out. The service has been excellent. They do not rush you to get out.  Never had a problem. Parking is plentiful. The staff is friendly and accommodating.

data.title: GOOD PLACE TO EAT
data.text: This restaurant should NOT be confused with the one on NW 7th Ave. or the one in Pembroke Pines. They are owned by different people. I go here for breakfast or dinner. The food is always good. Prices are a little high but you get a lot of food. Seldom have a server issue but lately they have a lot of new servers. Good variety menu and have daily specials.
